Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with geometric packing problems. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithm for approximating the optimal solution. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the problem involves discrete geometric objects and constraints. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) may be relevant as the paper discusses approximation algorithms and the concept of PTAS (polynomial time approximation scheme). 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) may be relevant as the paper discusses the impossibility of achieving a PTAS for certain cases.
